<seg id=1> Shanghai To Host World Trade Organization and China Services and Trade Symposium </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Shanghai, April 15 (Xia Ruge reporting with intern journalist Zhang Jiansong): "The World Trade Organization and China Services and Trade Symposium" will convene in Shanghai on April 19. WTO Director-General Renato Ruggiero will speak at the meeting. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to reports, the symposium's main topic will be China's promises, made  during talks concerning the country's entry into the WTO, to open up various aspects of the service and trade industry. These aspects include finances, insurance, marine shipping, consulting, the retail industry, advertising, lawyers and accountants. Also up for discussion is how their opening up will affect those in the same fields in the domestic market, along with how competitive each field is internationally. The Chinese government is in the midst of talks concerning how best to control the level of openness of the services and trade industry. </seg>
<seg id=4> The symposium will also investigate future pilot joint ventures that are to be set up in Shanghai. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The two-day symposium will be jointly held by the Shanghai Research Center of the WTO and the Foreign Services Limited Company of Shanghai. </seg>
<seg id=6> Long Yongtu, Vice-minister of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) and a past attendee to General Agreement on Tariff and Trade talks, and Shen Jueren, former MOFTEC Vice-minister, will attend the symposium along with Mr. Ruggiero. </seg>
<seg id=7> About two hundred people will attend in total, including MOFTEC committee members, leaders of large corporations, experts and academics. </seg>
</p>
